description: [``botocore``] Update cloudwatch client to latest version
[``botocore``] Updated ResourceType enum with new resource types onboarded by AWS Config in April 2023.
[``botocore``] Remove unused InvalidParameterException from CreateParticipant API
[``botocore``] Documentation update for new error type NamespaceNotFoundException for CreateCluster and UpdateCluster
[``botocore``] This release adds support for the Suricata REJECT option in midstream exception configurations.
[``botocore``] DescribeDomainNodes: A new API that provides configuration information for nodes part of the domain
[``botocore``] Add support for Topic, Dataset parameters and VPC

[``botocore``] This release adds a new attribute FaceOccluded. Additionally, you can now select attributes individually (e.g. ["DEFAULT", "FACE_OCCLUDED", "AGE_RANGE"] instead of ["ALL"]), which can reduce response time.

[``botocore``] We added support for ml.inf2 and ml.trn1 family of instances on Amazon SageMaker for deploying machine learning (ML) models for Real-time and Asynchronous inference. You can use these instances to achieve high performance at a low cost for generative artificial intelligence (AI) models.
[``botocore``] This release enables customers to call SQS using AWS JSON-1.0 protocol.
